Aoife Name Meaning in English

What does the name Aoife mean? What is the meaning of the name Aoife, lucky number, lucky stone, origin and religion.

Means "beauty" from the Gaelic word aoibh. In Irish legend Aoife was a warrior princess. In war against her sister Scathach, she was defeated in single combat by the hero Cúchulainn. ... This name is sometimes used as a Gaelic form of EVE or EVA.

Aoife Name Meaning, Origin & Details

Meaning: Life Short Info: Aoife was a daughter of King Dermot of Leinster. She married the Richard de Claire, also known as Strongbow, the leader of the Norman invasion of Ireland in 1169. Details: From the Irish Gaelic aoibh, meaning "beauty". Could also be an Irish version of the name Eve. Gender: Girl Origin: Gaelic Religion: Christian Suitable for: Girls / Female / Women Hardness: Easy to pronounce, Aoife is a short name Uniqueness: It is a common name Short & Easy: Yes Syllables: 5 Letters and 1 Words
